  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But because the Lord loved you,.... With an unmerited love; he loved them, because he loved them; that is, because he would love them; his love was not owing to any goodness in them, or done by them, or any love in them to him, but to his own good will and pleasure: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and because he would keep the oath which he had sworn unto your fathers; the promise he had made, confirmed by an oath: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "hath the Lord brought you out with a mighty hand; out of the land of Egypt: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and redeemed you out of the house of bondmen; where they were bondmen to the Egyptians: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt; who detained them, and refused to let them go. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt; who detained them, and refused to let them go. ",
