      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Because the Lord loved you.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Targum Onkelos, \"Because he had complacency in you;\" Vulgate, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "quia vobis junctus est",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"Instead of saying, He hath chosen you out of love to your fathers, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Moses brings out in this place love to the people of Israel as the Divine motive, not for choosing Israel, but for leading it out and delivering it from the slave-house of Egypt, by which God had practically carried out the election of the people, that he might thereby allure the Israelites to a reciprocity of love\" (Keil). Deuteronomy 7:8",
        "children": []
      },
